omp\">comp</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/ExternalProduct/Basic.html#CategoryTheory.MonoidalCategory.externalProduct\">externalProduct</a> <span class=\"fn\">H'</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given an extension `α : H ⟶ L ⋙ H'`, this is the canonical extension\n`H ⊠ K ⟶ L.prod (𝟭 E) ⋙ H' ⊠ K` it induces through bifunctoriality of the external product. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/ExternalProduct/KanExtension.html#CategoryTheory.MonoidalCategory.ExternalProduct.extensionUnitLeft","kind":"def","line":38,"name":"CategoryTheory.MonoidalCategory.ExternalProduct.extensionUnitLeft","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Monoidal/ExternalProduct/KanExtension.lean#L38-L41"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.ExternalProduct.Basic","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Functor.KanExtension.Pointwise","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Limits.Final"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.ExternalProduct.KanExtension"}